                            h3.mb-0 Battleship | C# Console Application
                            .subheading.mb-3 A simple console app created using C# to get familiarized with C# and .NET
                            div 
                            p Moving head first into C# and to the classes and object-oriented programming was a big shift in thinking from Javascript. The best way forward was through, so I bought a big book and grabbed an online tutorial and began learning. And just when I was beginning to feel comfortable Javascript, I had to start all over again. No problem though, I enjoy learning and relish the idea of picking up new languages. Learning C# and seeing how much it can do is awe-inspiring to me. I had a to really think about how I wanted to structure my program. Using a 2D array I managed to display a game grid with numbers to indicated columns and rows. Creating the game logic was where things got difficult. I had to devise a way of keeping track of all the different variables like hit count, shot count, and the battleship location. Through encapsulation, and by singling out a Player class, a Battleship class, and  a Display class, I was able to separate concerns and make the program extensible in the future. Upon completing this app I was primed in C# and ready for more opportunity to use my newfound knowledge.
