                            .subheading.mb-3 A game created to practice object oriented programming principles
                            div 
                            p Creating games, I've seen, is a great way to get acquianted with a programming language. I had some previous experience with Javascript, but not this in depth. I felt my past projects were very simple and lacked any complex logic. One of the biggest challenges I faced while constructing this app was to get a snake object to move around the board, pick up an apple, and then have the snake grow another segment. Accomplishing this through using arrays and popping off the last segment when the snake moved out of the square, while not the most efficient in terms of big O, but I felt was a creative solution to a nagging problem. Once I had the boundary detection logic coded, I wanted to add a feature of scoring. I especially wanted to the results to be saved locally, giving me another opportunity to flex my brain muscle. This app really drove home concepts of object oriented programming that at the start were quite weak and needed some refinement. 
